<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="41" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="41">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="41">
Described from Puerto Rico, America on 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Panicum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Panicum" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="41" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">Panicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
leaves, this species is recorded from Egypt and Uganda by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1365-3113.1975.tb00135.x" author="Ritchie, JM" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Entomology (B)" pageId="0" pageNumber="41" pagination="261 - 282" refId="B14" refString="Ritchie, JM, 1974. A revision of the grass-living genus Podothrips (Thysanoptera: Phlaeothripidae. Journal of Entomology (B) 43: 261 - 282" title="A revision of the grass-living genus Podothrips (Thysanoptera: Phlaeothripidae." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1365-3113.1975.tb00135.x" volume="43" year="1974">Ritchie (1974)</bibRefCitation>
, with 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. aegyptiacus" pageId="0" pageNumber="41" rank="species" species="aegyptiacus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">P. aegyptiacus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Priesner placed as a synonym. This is one of two species from China in which the thorax is yellow (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 17–22" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 17 - 22. Podothrips adult colour patterns 17 P. lucasseni 18 P. odonaspicola 19 P. semiflavus 20 P. femoralis sp. nov. 21 P. sasacola. Some important features of femoralis sp. nov. 22 mesopresternum and metathoracic sternopleural sutures. Scale bars: 200 microns." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.882.39029.figures17-22" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/349333" pageId="0" pageNumber="41" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.882.39029.figures17-22">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
), but 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. luteus" pageId="0" pageNumber="41" rank="species" species="luteus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">P. luteus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Taiwan has abdominal segments 
<normalizedToken originalValue="VIII–X">VIII-X</normalizedToken>
brown, whereas the abdomen of 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. semiflavus" pageId="0" pageNumber="41" rank="species" species="semiflavus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">P. semiflavus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is almost yellow with just the basal third of the tube brown (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 17–22" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 17 - 22. Podothrips adult colour patterns 17 P. lucasseni 18 P. odonaspicola 19 P. semiflavus 20 P. femoralis sp. nov. 21 P. sasacola. Some important features of femoralis sp. nov. 22 mesopresternum and metathoracic sternopleural sutures. Scale bars: 200 microns." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.882.39029.figures17-22" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/349333" pageId="0" pageNumber="41" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.882.39029.figures17-22">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
). One female from Guangdong has been studied here, and this is the first record of the species from China.
</paragraph>
